# GitHub Copilot repository instructions - SolverFin

SolverFin is a financial control product for personal finance, MEI, autonomous professionals and small businesses. Prioritize safety, traceability, LGPD/privacy and clear financial domain boundaries.

## Build and validation
Use the commands documented in README. If commands are not available yet, add or update them as part of repository bootstrap issues.
Expected validation categories: install, lint, typecheck, tests, build and database migration validation.

## Product rules
- Keep personal, MEI and business contexts separated.
- Every financial record must belong to a user/tenant/profile.
- AI-generated suggestions must be reviewable and auditable.
- Do not silently delete financial data; prefer soft delete and audit trail.
- Do not log secrets, raw bank messages or full card/account identifiers.

## Implementation style
- Make focused changes tied to the issue.
- Prefer explicit types and schemas for API inputs and AI outputs.
- Add tests for domain rules, tenant isolation and import/deduplication logic.
- Update docs and ADRs when changing architecture, data model or public API contracts.
